column7: Welcome to sh404SEF!
column8:
To enable it for your site, use the main Enable URL optimization Yes/No selector and press the Save button. sh404SEF will start with its default settings, suitable in most cases.

Please check out the documentation

column7: You may need to enable the language filter plugin.
column8: It seems your site is multilingual. From sh404SEF version 4.3.1 up, Joomla! languagefilter system plugin should now be enabled, while older versions required it to be disabled. You can enable it on this page

Joomla SEF settings are probably not correct
column8: Joomla! and sh404SEF SEF URLs settings don't match. Check that Joomla! SEF URLs are enabled. Check also that if you enabled Adds Suffix to URL, you also added a File suffix in sh404SEF configuration. This is not required by sh404SEF but some extensions may not work properly.
